{
  "doc_id": "44446",
  "text": "Risk factors for postpartum depression have been extensively assessed in general community samples of postpartum women. Three meta-analyses consistently identified moderate to strong associations between postpartum depressive symptoms and history of depression, prenatal depression or anxiety, low selfesteem, stressful life events, and poor social support [CITATION_1] . In contrast, relatively fewer studies have assessed risk factors for depression in NICU mothers [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] and/or anxiety [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . The results of these studies varied widely and are, therefore, not conclusive.",
